commit_message:
Support reviewers stats for stable branches

Adds a "-s" option that lets you specify the name of a stable branch
(for example "-s havana") instead of specifying a project (-p) or all
projects (-a).

reviewers.py will then use a specific stable.json file that defines the
set of projects stable-maint-core has authority on, as well as the
contents of that core team.

Note: -s disables result caching since the search is made on
specific branches, which would pollute the general purpose cache.

Change-Id: Idd03f51c98e006972bc93e3ce11e052cd1cc26aa

commit_message:
allow overriding all endpoint hosts with a single attribute

similar to the pattern in the messaging and database attributes, this is
a convenience change that allows you to set all endpoint host values to
something other than the default of 127.0.0.1, by only overriding a
single attribute in your environment.

Quite often one will want to set all endpoints to the same IP, for
example in the case where you are deploying a 'controller' node, and at
the moment every endpoint host attribute has to be overridden
individually.

All endpoint host attributes can still be overridden individually if
desired.

Change-Id: I7dd96f69c3eaa9156513663f08dafbddf1c1ffd8

commit_message:
Show error in login page in Unauthorized exception

When user hits an 'Unauthorized' exception, redirect to login page,
and show error in popup message.

This is a follow up fix for problem in:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/24604

Above fix changed Horzon to popup error message instead of redirect
to login page, in order to provide user error details. However,
this behavior may send exception page to user directly, because
there are lots of unhandled 'Unauthorized' exception in Horizon.

This fix changes back to the old style of behavior that redirect
to login page, and show the actual error in popup message.

Change-Id: I26d5fe60ecca6c104f948f70717976e07f0f2009
Closes-Bug: #1252785

commit_message:
VMware: fix exception when using multiple compute nodes

When there is more than one compute node running and one of the
nodes restarts it terminates on an exception that the resource is
not found.

The cause of the issue is that a vif plug was being attempted for
a resource that did not exist. The vif plug should have raised an
"NotImplemented" exception.

Change-Id: I5a3f1cc73a981173b6c2fa493de3aad10a7e97fd
Closes-bug: #1272286

commit_message:
Allow concat fw-admin w/ other nets in serializer

For Neutron mode an orchestrator_serialiser does:
* Create a bridge 'br-fw-admin'
* Connect it to node.admin_interface
* It's allowed to connect other nets to node.admin_interface
* In GRE mode the bridge 'br-prv' is not created.
* Change an order of bridge creation to manadge right
  ordering of IP setup.
* Revert qickfixed changes in logic https://review.openstack.org/#/c/72563
* Revert qickfixed changes in verifying https://review.openstack.org/#/c/72606

Closes-bug: 1278363
Change-Id: I5a9036c61cdd0099a25cfc6c153f48d7f3e56876

commit_message:
Skip a test for nicira service plugin

test_router_add_interface_subnet_with_port_from_other_tenant
is causing intermittent failures in unit tests because of
issues related with sql session autoflush.

This patch skips this test, since it is already covered
by another test case in the same module. This should prevent
job failures while the relevant bug is addressed.

commit_message:
Fix swift data source credential validation

The validation for swift data source credentials assumed that only the
elements within the credentials were missing. If the credentials
element itself was missing an internal error would be triggered.

Change-Id: I1c5d9673ae383eb8154508be01ceb67877b6e0cb
Closes-bug: #1277497

commit_message:
Add action_event_create and action_event_update api to conductor

This is the first one of patch series to support recording more event
details in action events. The current action_event_start /
action_event_finish functions always called in pair and lacks of
flexibility in order to inject a single event entry for debugging
purpose.

This patch preserves current action_event_start / action_event_finish
interface and behavior for compatiblity sake. The action_event_create
behaves just like action_event_start, however this function call doesn't
implicitly imply a subsequent 'finish' calls. And it can be used to
inject a one-shot entry for event record.

Implement: blueprint improve-instance-action-events
Change-Id: I82cdf9bea07ba4e39b54ff99946abbd3ec09bff6

and click "Submit" button,then the "Submit" button is disabled,

commit_message:
Remove using of deprecated self.headers (part1)

Attr self.headers in rest client is deprecated now, and
should be removed from usage by service clients.

This patch removes first bunch of attrs.
Second and last part is intended to be in another patch,
with removing from all other service clients
and from rest client itself.

Change-Id: I28981738a9e7f39343cf530c2642315f0a5b22f2
Partially-implements: bp refactor-rest-client

commit_message:
port nova v2 images related tests into nova v3 part2

In nova v3 api, there is no image api. So in nova v3
api tests, we just keep these tests related to create_image
action of the server api. Other tests are moved into glance
testing, also some tests is no longer available, as some
actions are just nova v2 api for glance proxy behaviour.
eg: update the specified item of image properties. In glance
we can only  update all values of image properties.

Partially implements blueprint nova-v3-api-tests

Change-Id: I89cec53f30f607b39ff2b4762d35c0f307cc634b

Adding new ssl extension for ssl-termination support
in neutron.
Extension is not served by lbaas plugin

Creating new abstract driver for ssl api
Adding new absract driver as a base to radware driver

Adding ssl dbmixin for ssl policies and certificates
management.
If service provider (driver) is not inheriting from new
abstract ssl driver - new "ExtensionNotSupportedByProvider"

Implements: blueprint lbaas-ssl-termination
'}]
commit_message:
New SSL extension

Adding new ssl extension for ssl-termination support
in neutron.
Extension is not served by lbaas plugin
but is extending lbaas vip with ssl entities associations

Creating new abstract driver for ssl api
Adding new absract driver as a base to radware driver

Adding ssl dbmixin for ssl policies and certificates
management.
If service provider (driver) is not inheriting from new
abstract ssl driver - new "ExtensionNotSupportedByProvider"
exception is raised.

Since association of ssl certificates and vip requires
sending a list on certificates, list support was needed
in neutron resource attributes parsing mechanism.
I added the lists support and extended unit tests to test it.

Added unit tests for extension and db mixin
Those tests flood up bug in other test
(tests/unit/test_extension_ext_gw_mode.TestL3GwModeMixin)
Bug #1279742 was opened for the issue.
Bug is fixed as part of this patch.

Change-Id: Ie96ebe3f35384468b8eab3b218238c8a1be92437
Implements: blueprint lbaas-ssl-termination

commit_message:
Only run the syncdb when set the session backend to sql.

From the horizon manual
http://docs.openstack.org/developer/horizon/topics/deployment.html#database,
we need the database only when set the session backend to sql, so we
just need run syncdb at that case.
Another reason I don't want to run this syncdb is, normally the web
application (here is the horizon) should not access the database server
directly in data center for security consideration.

Change-Id: I39323fc797bcb9a9b821e955d8f648a4271086b1

commit_message:
Ensure that bug number is actually a number for skip_because

This commit adds a regex check that bugs numbers passed into the
skip_because decorator are actually numbers. Previously any string
could be passed into the decorator which defeats the whole purpose of
the decorator.

revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2014-02-11 13:48:32.000000000', 'files': ['tox.ini'], 'message': 'Remove tox locale overrides

* tox.ini: The LANG, LANGUAGE and LC_ALL environment overrides were
introduced originally during the testr migration in an attempt to be
conservative about the possibility that locale settings in the
calling environment could cause consistency problems for test runs.
In actuality, this should be unnecessary and any place where it does
cause issues ought to be considered an actual bug. Also, having
these in the configuration actively causes older pip to have
problems with non-ASCII content in some package metadata files under
Python 3, so drop it now.

Change-Id: Ia910ded1789a1a8fac7d82f1ce97300ad7bfefda
Closes-Bug: #1277495
'}]
commit_message:
Remove tox locale overrides

* tox.ini: The LANG, LANGUAGE and LC_ALL environment overrides were
introduced originally during the testr migration in an attempt to be
conservative about the possibility that locale settings in the
calling environment could cause consistency problems for test runs.
In actuality, this should be unnecessary and any place where it does
cause issues ought to be considered an actual bug. Also, having
these in the configuration actively causes older pip to have
problems with non-ASCII content in some package metadata files under
Python 3, so drop it now.

Change-Id: Ia910ded1789a1a8fac7d82f1ce97300ad7bfefda
Closes-Bug: #1277495

commit_message:
Improve memory/performace in ManagerService

Added the event_get_first_sorted_by_filters method to the DB API.
The idea of this method is to only return the first event that
satisfies the sorting criteria and all the filters.

In the ManagerService class, replaced the use of
event_get_all_sorted_by_filters method for
event_get_first_sorted_by_filters in order to reduce the use of memory and
improve the performace.

Change-Id: I54491bae9dafb3ecf2adb29aae6bb8139c8751b4
Closes-Bug: #1279459

commit_message:
Add API schema for v3 quota_classes API

By defining the API schema, it is possible to separate the validation
code from the API method. The API method can be more simple.
In addition, a response of API validation error can be consistency for
whole of Nova APIs.

Partially implements blueprint nova-api-validation-fw

commit_message:
enable volume list tests for cinder v2 - part2

this ports test_volumes_list into cinder v2 api,
and also ports corresponding client.

1. changes of the response data of list and list details in v2:
(their items are same in v1)
- list view includes items:
id, name, link
- list details view includes items:
id, status, size, availability_zone,created_at, attachments, name,
description, volume_type, snapshot_id, source_volid, metadata,
links, user_id, bootable

2. use 'name' instead of 'display_name'

v2 commit id:
0c507aa6d08a9471bf896961cc99d40f337f1e4d
484fb9e1c748e718349e451e80a0e025ed007b1d

Change-Id: I19cf00270f0ca55770188c6c71c02e13c5bd82f6

counts.

commit_message:
Add "body=" argument to v3 API unit tests

This patch adds "body=" argument to v3 API unit tests for avoiding
the test failures due to KeyError when applying the API validation
framework to "create a server" API.

_process_stack() of nova's wsgi passes kwargs which includes 'body'
like:
    {'body': {u'server': {u'name': u'my-server', [..]}}}
to an API method. The validation framework finds a body with the
keyword 'body' from the kwargs, and validates the body with the API
schema. So this changes is also for fitting the arguments to the wsgi
behavior.

Partially implements blueprint nova-api-validation-fw

Change-Id: Id5fa416e021b529e20aca3701e3f159bb316e7fb

subject: Cleanup oauth tests
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2014-02-13 00:10:14.000000000', 'files': ['keystone/tests/test_v3_oauth1.py'], 'message': 'Cleanup oauth tests

In a lot of places this code was using dict.get() where [] makes
more sense because the code then assumes that the field was
present and had a value. Using .get() just means that if the code
changes the error would be an unexpected TypeError on a different
line than where the problem actually was.

Also, building of simple url strings was simplified to remove the
dict so that they could be kept on a single line.

Change-Id: I98b5631e02fe1456f0f583c4ec55c9ac0f8c4c35
'}]
commit_message:
Cleanup oauth tests

In a lot of places this code was using dict.get() where [] makes
more sense because the code then assumes that the field was
present and had a value. Using .get() just means that if the code
changes the error would be an unexpected TypeError on a different
line than where the problem actually was.

Also, building of simple url strings was simplified to remove the
dict so that they could be kept on a single line.

commit_message:
Correctly normalize consumer fields on update

The self._normalize_dict() function in ConsumerCrudV3 creates a
copy of the consumer passed in and doesn't modify it, so this
line of code didn't do anything. The code is changed to use the
result as the new consumer rather than discarding it.

Closes-Bug: #1276857
Change-Id: Iec7573001ad73f0dc9192a4e74b1c35adc2cda4c

commit_message:
Revert to previous status if volume busy on delete

Currently when deleting a volume and it is busy, the manager will set
the status to 'available', even if the volume was in an error state.
The solution here is to save the previous state in the volume's
admin_metadata, and set to that.

Change-Id: I8e983d6e8e51b0ac8c43f773168a823b239be85b
Closes-Bug: #1236165

commit_message:
Prevent E500 when delayed delete is enabled

If delayed delete is enabled the user token was not being propagated
properly to the registry in all cases. This resulted in an authentication
error when the API attempted to connect to the registry, which in turn
caused a 500 error from the API.

Fix for bug 1238604.

Change-Id: Ifafc1613db034508abfce7ba5e4df582e6056c10

commit_message:
Fix volume transfer tests with tenant isolation disabled

This commit fixes the volume transfer tests for when tenant isolation
is disabled. The volume transfer tests still had a reference to the old
auth style to get the tenant name if tenant isolation was disabled.
The recent auth_provider refactor didn't update this call so the test
would fail. This commit updates it to use the new credential dict to
get the tenant_name

Change-Id: Ie7fe39baf6f62fa6966631d7890891252602ed8d

commit_message:
refactor keystone.conf template specs

add tests for every tunable.  organize code layout to reflect actual
template layout (group tests, in order).  also 3x performance gain by
collapsing 50+ chef converges into one.  remove 'pending' tests in
other platforms since there are no platform-specific tunables.

commit_message:
Make live migration validation optional

This live migration validation can leave the system locked, this patch
can help resolve those issues. Take an example: if the VM instance was
created with force host option, then the VM instance will not be able
to be migrated when checking scheduler hints. Thus, an option
'validate_by_scheduler' was introudced in order to make this validation
optional.

Co-Author: Yassine Lamgarchal <yassine.lamgarchal@enovance.com>

DocImpact
'validate_by_scheduler' was introduced to make live migration validation
optinoal.

Change-Id: I9a0e887ed385fd1a5808e4fe541cd83ac8a87c37
Implements part of bp validate-targethost-live-migration

[{'number': 18, 'created': '2014-02-15 17:31:22.000000000', 'files': ['keystone/tests/test_v3_oauth1.py', 'keystone/common/sql/migration.py', 'keystone/tests/test_v3_federation.py', 'keystone/tests/test_associate_project_endpoint_extension.py', 'keystone/cli.py'], 'message': 'Correct `find_migrate_repo` usage

The `find_migrate_repo` function was never used with an argument although the
function interface presupposes an optional argument named
`package`.

$ grep -r "find_migrate_repo" keystone

    keystone/common/sql/migration.py: repo_path = find_migrate_repo()
    keystone/common/sql/migration.py: repo_path = find_migrate_repo()
    keystone/common/sql/migration.py: repo_path = find_migrate_repo()

The wrong function usage makes the function redundant (only one
string is needed there, all others are never executed) and forces redundant
code lines in other modules.
Database migration functions must take an extension module object and handle
a migration repository path with `find_migrate_repo` function.

::db_sync: [version, [package]]
::db_version: [package]
::db_version_control: [version, [package]]

`find_migrate_repo` raises an error when the migrate repository path doesn't
exist. The error should be handled to prevent further unexpected behaviour.

Closes-Bug: #1273336
Change-Id: Id62a1859a7e72139d25dfe91d29805660b4b7394
'}]
commit_message:
Correct `find_migrate_repo` usage

The `find_migrate_repo` function was never used with an argument although the
function interface presupposes an optional argument named
`package`.

$ grep -r "find_migrate_repo" keystone

    keystone/common/sql/migration.py: repo_path = find_migrate_repo()
    keystone/common/sql/migration.py: repo_path = find_migrate_repo()
    keystone/common/sql/migration.py: repo_path = find_migrate_repo()

The wrong function usage makes the function redundant (only one
string is needed there, all others are never executed) and forces redundant
code lines in other modules.
Database migration functions must take an extension module object and handle
a migration repository path with `find_migrate_repo` function.

::db_sync: [version, [package]]
::db_version: [package]
::db_version_control: [version, [package]]

`find_migrate_repo` raises an error when the migrate repository path doesn't
exist. The error should be handled to prevent further unexpected behaviour.

Closes-Bug: #1273336
Change-Id: Id62a1859a7e72139d25dfe91d29805660b4b7394

Several clients support printing dict with unicode using method

commit_message:
Use `six.text_type` instead of `str` in cliutils

Several clients support printing dict with unicode using method
`print_dict`.

Using `unicode()` does not satisfy the Python 3 compatibility, so
we need to use `six.text_type` to allow print dict with unicode and
to support both Python 2 and 3.

Related to bp make-python3-compatible

Change-Id: If87fba3a5a53d2d6a97bd6d2cae6779b7dc81eed

Messaging backend selection

There is another patch that removes rabbitmq-server from
boot-stack's element dependencies.

https://review.openstack.org/#/c/72516/

This patch selects rabbitmq-server as the default messaging
backend using the *EXTRA_ARGS environment variable.

commit_message:
Use database connection for keystone

The keystone configuration used the 'connection' option in the
'sql' section of the keystone.conf file. This option is deprecated
in favor of 'connection' in the 'database' section.

The keystone setup code is changed to use the option in the new
section rather than the deprecated one.

Change-Id: I62fd2f50ded3b8848e9e5225e88c80ed8fed3bff

Adds Parameter Label to HOT spec and parameter schema

This change will add the ability to put a human readable label
in a HOT Template for each parameter. This label will be used
to provide a better form label in any user interface when
available.

commit_message:
Update Object Storage API Reference

Point to WADL files that generate the API Reference
  page so that the method descriptions and request
  and response parameters are consistent between
  these two docs:
    http://api.openstack.org/api-ref-objectstorage.html
      (API Reference page for Object Storage)
    http://docs.openstack.org/api/openstack-object-storage/1.0/
      (API Reference (or spec) for Object Storage)

Add descriptions of ACLs, FormPOST, TempURLs,
  StaticWeb, Bulk Upload, Bulk Delete, the OPTIONS operation
  (though this is implicit in CORS support)

Validate all code examples

Remove duplication.

Co-Author: Donagh McCabe

Closes-Bug: #1187119
Closes-Bug: #1214139
Closes-Bug: #1074198
Partial-Bug: #1255770

commit_message:
alembic with initial migration and tests

All sqlalchemy migrations and code associated
with them was removed including tests

Added all necessery alembic code to expose alembic specific features:
like revision and stamp

Added initial migration for alembic, that is fully in sync with models
including: uniques, indexes and columns params

Refactored test_versions to use alembic as migration api

Refactored BaseTestCase and Database fixture to use alembic as migration api

Change-Id: I8a91704d21ccea1b8135b9d724df5856ac21108c

commit_message:
Don't skip tests for some bugs

Skipping tests for a bug is a bad idea since if the bug is fixed
it's a manual process to find the affected test rather than being
found automatically by the tests.

commit_message:
Further preparation for transition to guest agent

 * Added abstract classes defining remote interface. The first class
   is for driver and the second one is for remote object. Note:
   execute_on_vm_interactive is not included into the later interface
   as it is not used in anywhere.
 * Now driver can provide additional part for userdata. This will be
   used by agent driver to setup guest agent on instances.
 * SSH opts are moved from ssh_remote.py to remote.py. While
   ssh_remote.py is the best place for them, together with change #1
   opts created circular imports:
     * remote.py imports ssh_remote.py to get options
     * ssh_remote.py imports remote.py to get abstract classes
   The problem can be resolved by moving abstract classes to a new
   module, say remote_common.py. But I prefer the variant I've
   implemented.
 * Fixed tests to work with the changes.

Implements: blueprint guest-agent
Change-Id: I2ccae4df7b664c612fd15a3e9578af5b7dd6f81c

commit_message:
Correct PXEPrivateMethodsTestCase.setUp

Unit tests within the PXEPrivateMethodsTestCase test class have been
sporadically failing on py26 test nodes since f14dacb7. That commit
introduced tests that interacted with the DB without inheriting from
DbTestCase, and loaded a driver via stevedore without mocking the
extension manager loading.

This patch corrects the above ommissions.

Change-Id: I2f930db7d3bb8abe120ce24a604f800c2e861fca
Closes-bug: #1279992

commit_message:
Make live LDAP user DN match the default from devstack

The default LDAP user DN in devstack uses the "cn" attribute in
the RDN.  The live LDAP test default configuration is supposed to
match the default devstack config, but the RDN is incorrectly
using the "dc" attribute.  This patch corrects the live LDAP
default config to match devstack.

Change-Id: Iee49606526047105b4e60142af32b4ec81a19444
Closes-Bug: 1280509

commit_message:
Storwize/SVC: Add delim to lsfabric

The lsfabric command in the Storwize/SVC omitted the delimeter and so
the output was not correctly parsed by the driver. This patch simply
adds it. Also make sure we are comparing lower-case WWPNs to ensure
host lookup success.

Change-Id: I50360401c4b12c8c38b7b433be660a65dd2fbda5
Closes-bug: 1279758

commit_message:
Skip curl pip package, if exists

It can save several seconds for dodgy network.
If the existing pip package is not in the good state,
the later tar operation will fail. Thus no need to worry
for using a wrong pip package

Change-Id: I1309a50d72d556acf21b6517235cedf442be3500

commit_message:
Added msg info in nova CLI when attaching volume

Added warning log message in nova CLI, in order to inform that device name may
not match the proposed one.
The intention is to provide more information when device names don't match due
to hypervisor limitations or naming convention.

commit_message:
some params for create flavor incorrectly checked

The flavor parameters name, ram, vcpus and disk for create flavor are
not checked correctly. When create flavor without name, it throws
exception with message:"name is not a string or unicode". I think it
should throw exception with message:"name must be specified for
flavor creation". The param ram, vcpus and disk have the same problem.
Because it didn't check whether the body contains the param.

Change-Id: I74feacd5e336d4a67948849769420c54a56bdae1
Closes-Bug: #1253525

commit_message:
Support building wheels (PEP-427)

Universal is used to identify pure-Python module(by bdist_wheel). For
these, it is sufficient to build a wheel with _any_ Python ABI version
and publish that to PyPI (by whatever means).

commit_message:
Avoid processing ports which are not yet ready

This patch changes get_vif_port_set in order to not return
OVS ports for which the ofport is not yet assigned, thus avoiding
a regex match failure in get_vif_port_by_id.
Because of this failure, treat_vif_port is unable to wire
the port.
As get_vif_port_by_id is also used elsewhere in the agent, it has
been enhanced in order to tolerate situations in which ofport might
have not yet been assigned.

The ofport field is added to the list of those monitored by the
SimpleInterfaceMonitor. This will guarantee an event is generated
when the ofport is assigned to a port. Otherwise there is a risk
a port would be never processed if it was not yet ready the first
time is was detected. This change won't trigger any extra processing
on the agent side.

Finally, this patch avoids fetching device details from the plugin
for ports which have disappeared from the OVS bridge. This is a
little optimization which might be beneficial for short lived ports.

Change-Id: Icf7f0c7d6fe5239a358567cc9dc9db8ec11c15be
Partial-Bug: #1253896

revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2014-02-11 09:44:44.000000000', 'files': ['tox.ini'], 'message': 'Have tox install via setup.py develop

tox 1.6 was released, which means that we can now take advantage of
the feature we added to it - which is using setup.py develop to
install the code into the virtualenv. The logic was taken from
run_tests.sh - so the performance issues around using tox vs. using
install_venv should now be gone.

Additionally, override the tox pip install command to avoid using
the "--pre" option which is the default in tox. "--pre" means
"Include pre-release and development versions." By default, pip will
only install stable versions of software, and that is the behavior
we want.

Change-Id: Ida5e440d1bdb9f8e9031277ea53a02d2ef171438
Co-Authored-By: Monty Taylor <mordred@inaugust.com>
'}]
commit_message:
Have tox install via setup.py develop

tox 1.6 was released, which means that we can now take advantage of
the feature we added to it - which is using setup.py develop to
install the code into the virtualenv. The logic was taken from
run_tests.sh - so the performance issues around using tox vs. using
install_venv should now be gone.

Additionally, override the tox pip install command to avoid using
the "--pre" option which is the default in tox. "--pre" means
"Include pre-release and development versions." By default, pip will
only install stable versions of software, and that is the behavior
we want.

Change-Id: Ida5e440d1bdb9f8e9031277ea53a02d2ef171438
Co-Authored-By: Monty Taylor <mordred@inaugust.com>

commit_message:
Add searchDepth when getClusterInfo called.

Without searchDepth, getClusterInfo shows every volume and
snapshot. It's an unused information and takes very long time.

Change-Id: Id590e3023f4446f01b965baf4e8ac61980101067
Closes-Bug: 1276388

commit_message:
Add EMC SMI-S FC Driver in Cinder

Add an EMC SMI-S FC Driver in Cinder. It supports all required
driver features.
Also made enhancements to the existing SMI-S iSCSI Driver
(performance enhancement, multiple pool support and thick/thin
provisioning, extend volume).
emc_smis_common.py is the common code used by both iSCSI driver
(emc_smis_iscsi.py) and FC driver (emc_smis_fc.py).

Implements blueprint emc-fibre-channel-volume-driver

Change-Id: Idace398ef60863811911511bcbbfcecb3bf58270

commit_message:
fix templatetag for no fractional bytes

In django 1.6, testing 0.0005 MB fails due to rounding issues.

Since a fractional byte makes no sense, just casting the float
value to an int.

Partially-implements: blueprint django-1point6
Change-Id: Id82faf32f0670f6342dac87a08affc10c7fda8de

If multiple instance types in a cell had the same memory_mb value or
root_gb + ephemeral_gb added to the same value, then capacity counts
would be inaccurate since slots would get counted multiple times.
Rather than counting based on instance type it is now based on the set

Closes-bug: #1276728
'}]
commit_message:
Count memory and disk slots once in cells state manager

If multiple instance types in a cell had the same memory_mb value or
root_gb + ephemeral_gb added to the same value, then capacity counts
would be inaccurate since slots would get counted multiple times.
Rather than counting based on instance type it is now based on the set
of memory or disk values pulled from instance types.

Change-Id: Iaded7fa69dadb4aa0335ef1569975bdfcb2767c6
Closes-bug: #1276728

commit_message:
Flavor show api will not show deleted flavors

* Do not show deleted flavors for flavor show api call
* Return deleted flavor details with v3 server show api call
* Not showing deleted flavors because flavor id are not unique
  for deleted/non-deleted flavors and this can return duplicates during
  "nova show"/ server show api call

Closes-Bug: #1153926
Change-Id: Ia38a6ad64f2c216b50c5a955a4f3f6d66f6424da

commit_message:
Unneeded identity reg done for api-cfn

When the heat cloud formation (api-cfn recipe) is not needed and
not used, the identity recipe still creates service and endpoint
identity registrations for it. I added a check to see if the
api-cfn recipe is in the run_list, suggestions welcome for better
ways to approach this.

Change-Id: I5f326a66f005f0553aecd8cea798a224d76f57c4
Closes-bug: 1279577

The default for reserved_host_memory_mb is 512 MB but because the
vCenter driver reports memory available to the VMs, VMware suggests

 VMwareVCDriver configuration options section

Closes-Bug: #1267303
'}]
commit_message:
Added recommendation for reserved_host_memory_mb value

The default for reserved_host_memory_mb is 512 MB but because the
vCenter driver reports memory available to the VMs, VMware suggests
setting this value to 0 MB. Added this recommendation to the
 VMwareVCDriver configuration options section

Change-Id: I11e01ff36a4d91c2c268b2ece65b4e7e19990468
Closes-Bug: #1267303

commit_message:
fix ips to 'ips' in APIRouter

Actually ips in `ips in init_only` would not be valued as True because
ips is a moudle object not a string. Fixing this to string 'ips' could
prevent potential issues and improve readability.

Change-Id: I74564349e1fef00e7430cfb0547b3ad87c8e471c

commit_message:
Store scheduler_hints in instance_system_metadata when create instance

Store scheduler_hints in instance_system_metadata when create instance,
the scheduler_hints can be later used by live migration or evacuate for
host validation.

Co-Author: Yassine Lamgarchal <yassine.lamgarchal@enovance.com>

Implements part of bp validate-targethost-live-migration

commit_message:
Support peer discovery through the metadata service

Adds an endpoint to the openstack metadata service to support peer discovery.
A GET on http://169.254.169.254/openstack/latest/peers.json returns a JSON
list of instances in the same project. This can be used to seed a node list
for a gossip protocol.

Change-Id: I76c912e7cd6c417b042567a55fb5869f5a22608e
Implements: blueprint first-discover-your-peers

commit_message:
Convert use_neutron_default_nets to BoolOpt

This option is boolean by nature, and setting it to StrOpt causes confusion.
For example, if you set this to 'true' in config file:

use_neutron_default_nets=true

then Nova will not use default nets, as string value is 'true', not 'True'.
Changing this to BoolOpt fixes this issue and makes the code more consistent.

Change-Id: Ib018fbff7a94af499dc1f44dab4f5353613cc721

commit_message:
Change package action to :upgrade

To achieve both uniformity and least surprise, it might be better to
always upgrade packages.  Before this change, it only installed some,
upgraded others.

If noone disagrees, I will change these package resources to honor
platform overrides and the corresponding tests.  (Feedback welcome :)

commit_message:
Volume-Host affinity weight which uses Ceilometer

Added a new weight for the filter scheduler that gets data from
ceilometer, if available, and uses it to determine the host where a
volume is placed, allowing the weight to give a good score to this host
or a bad score to any other.

Change-Id: I0e6d052a63e728e16538de7e5229e3cda9b0cc8f
Implements: blueprint cross-service-filter-scheduling

Now in OpenStack nova, we support live migration, cold migration
and resize.

For live migration, we do not need to confirm after live migration

For resize, we need to confirm, as we want to give end user an
opportunity to rollback.

commit_message:
Auto confirm cold migration by default

Now in OpenStack nova, we support live migration, cold migration
and resize.

For live migration, we do not need to confirm after live migration
finished.

For resize, we need to confirm, as we want to give end user an
opportunity to rollback.

The problem is cold migration, because cold migration and resize
share same code path, so once admin submit a cold migration request
and after the cold migration finished, the VM will goes to
verify_resize state, and admin needs to confirm resize. Nova should
support auto confirm cold migration by default.

UpgradeImpact
DocImpact
A new parameter was introduced: cold_migration_confirm_window, it
will only handle auto confirm for cold migration.
1) Set to 0 to disable auto confirm to cold migration
2) Set to N to auto confirm cold migrations after N seconds
3) Default value is 1

Implements bp auto-confirm-cold-migration
Change-Id: I2d41a9267be27b109c22dea40b061967513353f8

commit_message:
Make sure the path of default storage pool is used

Seed machine image got created at /var/lib/libvirt/images (the default
path for the default storage pool) even if this location has been
altered.

This patch ensures that the correct path is used, by checking the path
first.

Change-Id: I3e4ccff301524b8f08bba7099fafe5a9b4d3442c
Closes-Bug: #1276277

[{'number': 5, 'created': '2014-01-17 13:25:22.000000000', 'files': ['horizon/__init__.py'], 'message': "Remove asserts for optional imports

Horizon's __init__.py has some code that explicitly allows it to
be imported by setup.py before Django is set up, by making import
failures just throw a warning instead of an exception. But that code
is defeated by a bunch of asserts that were added later, that just
make the error even more confusing.

I'm removing the asserts and replacing them with __all__.

Closes-bug: #1210253
Change-Id: I0fde7810a033fd7216da9a5460f5e4e323b4d6e9
(cherry picked from commit b6eb9a2480a82cf93f7a62e9c7373feddc8296fe)
"}]
commit_message:
Remove asserts for optional imports

Horizon's __init__.py has some code that explicitly allows it to
be imported by setup.py before Django is set up, by making import
failures just throw a warning instead of an exception. But that code
is defeated by a bunch of asserts that were added later, that just
make the error even more confusing.

I'm removing the asserts and replacing them with __all__.

Closes-bug: #1210253
Change-Id: I0fde7810a033fd7216da9a5460f5e4e323b4d6e9
(cherry picked from commit b6eb9a2480a82cf93f7a62e9c7373feddc8296fe)

commit_message:
Migrate opt_in_group() and opt() to a fixture

Create a configuration fixture to support registering arbitrary
configuration options and migrate away from the use of
opt_in_group() and opt().  Most uses of opt_in_group() calls
from .setUp() were moved into moved into the .config() method on
the test case class.

Change-Id: I94fd57f4e24826f26c5ab09779f0583737a9737a

commit_message:
Devtest Overcloud all-in-one support.

If OVERCLOUD_ALL_IN_ONE is set builds the overcloud
by using a single image. This is useful if you want
to save memory or only have access to a single
bare metal overcloud machine.

This is something we've supported in the old TOCI scripts and
it has proven useful to some of us.

For now the all-in-one commands are all undocumented.

Change-Id: I392322b79b4635d77047f020bbd40e4a4676ac28

Changing these will be reflected in the local_settings.py
configuration file.

Note that there are additional neutron options, however I've opted to
only do enable_lb and enable_quotas as we have a load balancer recipe
in the network cookbook, and enable_quotas defaults to True.  The
remaining neutron options can also be turned into attributes if/when we
support that functionality.

Change-Id: I6fd9f7df58f46861c6fa8d8c6ed502fb554d951e
"}]
commit_message:
Make more dashboard options configurable

This change adds the following new attributes:

node['openstack']['dashboard']['password_autocomplete']
node['openstack']['dashboard']['neutron']['enable_lb']
node['openstack']['dashboard']['neutron']['enable_quotas']

Changing these will be reflected in the local_settings.py
configuration file.

Note that there are additional neutron options, however I've opted to
only do enable_lb and enable_quotas as we have a load balancer recipe
in the network cookbook, and enable_quotas defaults to True.  The
remaining neutron options can also be turned into attributes if/when we
support that functionality.

Change-Id: I6fd9f7df58f46861c6fa8d8c6ed502fb554d951e

commit_message:
Update how dashboard's secret key is handled

Currently, you can override the 'secret_key_path' attribute but this
does not get reflected in the dashboard configuration.  This change
does the following:

- updates local_settings.py to use the specified secret key
- adds a default attribute for 'secret_key_content' which when set
overrides the contents of the secret key (useful if you have multiple
web servers running dashboard and they all need the same secret key)

Change-Id: Ia82947280a64f6b1ec693ee273ac386a71be57ad
Closes-Bug: #1279863

commit_message:
Adds support for the get_rdp_console API

Hyper-V employs RDP to access virtual machine consoles, unlike most
other hypervisors which support VNC.

In order to support this scenario, the get_rdp_console API has been
added to Nova. This commit adds the corresponding client side feature,
implemented in a way consistent with existing VNC and SPICE console
support.

Nova Gerrit commit: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/43502/

Change-Id: I86b814797d234f1eb49a7fa67ed27a9bcda034ae
Implements: blueprint hyper-v-rdp-console

commit_message:
Tune up report and downtime intervals for l2 agent

If the neutron server erroneously thinks than the l2 agent is down
it will fail to bind a port, which can lead to VM's spawn errors.

This patch aims to add support for agent checks flags.

Change-Id: If047c5d52d10a8ca9b1b765400bdd99a29550b1e
Signed-off-by: Emilien Macchi <emilien.macchi@enovance.com>

commit_message:
Fixing neutron::server connection parameter

Previously, neutron::server's (deprecated) sql_connection parameter
had a default value, preventing the new/preferred connection
parameter from ever being used.

This change removes that default, permitting the connection
parameter to work properly, and extends unit tests to confirm.

bug introduced at commit 82552e79316a4ffc1c879dd3aaa1f4735a4a35a0,

a code move only with some updated comments.  The functions are now

revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2014-02-11 18:16:16.000000000', 'files': ['stack.sh'], 'message': 'Install glance images before starting Nova

The docker driver for Nova needs a registry service to be running.
It is being run inside a container using an image -- that image must
be downloaded. The registry service must be started via
nova_plugins/hypervisor-docker, but this is presently called
before Glance's image download.

The reordering is being done such that Glance may download the
registry image, but prior to starting Nova such that "hypervisor-docker"
may have an image downloaded and available to launch the registry.

This change should cause no negative effects on other hypervisors.

commit_message:
Install glance images before starting Nova

The docker driver for Nova needs a registry service to be running.
It is being run inside a container using an image -- that image must
be downloaded. The registry service must be started via
nova_plugins/hypervisor-docker, but this is presently called
before Glance's image download.

The reordering is being done such that Glance may download the
registry image, but prior to starting Nova such that "hypervisor-docker"
may have an image downloaded and available to launch the registry.

This change should cause no negative effects on other hypervisors.

Change-Id: I7bccb42517e4c6187f2a90c64f39cda4577f89a3
blueprint: docker-glance-uploads

commit_message:
Cleanup cinder-rootwrap support

cinder_rootwrap support in devstack handled a number of now-abandoned
use cases:

- no $CINDER_DIR/etc/cinder/rootwrap.d (old-style rootwrap)
- using oslo-rootwrap instead of cinder-rootwrap (abandoned experiment)

This change removes unused code paths and aligns
configure_cinder_rootwrap() with configure_nova_rootwrap().

Change-Id: I387808dae0e064cc9c894c74ab78e86124f08dd2

commit_message:
Move install responsibilities to domU

As we are moving forward to test XenAPI in the gate, it is necessary to
move dom0 related modifications to be performed from domU. For this
purpose, a new user is created, and that user should be used to talk to
dom0 from domU. This change creates that user, makes it possible for
dom0 to log in to domU with that account, and configure that account to
be able to talk down to dom0.

Also move several steps to the nova xenserver plugin:
 - dom0 plugin installation
 - create kernels and images directory
 - install console rotate script
 - configure a cron to execute console rotate script

Configuration changes:
    A new configuration option, DOMZERO_USER has been created, that
    specifies a user account that is configured to be able to do
    passwordless ssh to dom0.

Change-Id: If9de0b297a67b7cdb5de78d8dd0e8b2ca578b601

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-02-10 14:27:59.000000000', 'files': ['tox.ini'], 'message': 'Remove tox locale overrides

* tox.ini: The LANG, LANGUAGE and LC_ALL environment overrides were
introduced originally during the testr migration in an attempt to be
conservative about the possibility that locale settings in the
calling environment could cause consistency problems for test runs.
In actuality, this should be unnecessary and any place where it does
cause issues ought to be considered an actual bug. Also, having
these in the configuration actively causes older pip to have
problems with non-ASCII content in some package metadata files under
Python 3, so drop it now.

Change-Id: I0661b20a0e426fee56bc706d364dfe158da9be72
Closes-Bug: #1277495
'}]
commit_message:
Remove tox locale overrides

* tox.ini: The LANG, LANGUAGE and LC_ALL environment overrides were
introduced originally during the testr migration in an attempt to be
conservative about the possibility that locale settings in the
calling environment could cause consistency problems for test runs.
In actuality, this should be unnecessary and any place where it does
cause issues ought to be considered an actual bug. Also, having
these in the configuration actively causes older pip to have
problems with non-ASCII content in some package metadata files under
Python 3, so drop it now.

Change-Id: I0661b20a0e426fee56bc706d364dfe158da9be72
Closes-Bug: #1277495

commit_message:
Raise requirement of Pep8 to 1.4.6

Pep8 1.4.6 has been released and can be required for Icehouse.
There are some noteworthy changes:

* Fix false positive E261/E262 when the file contains a BOM
* Fix E701, E702 and E703 not detected sometimes
* Fix E122 not detected in some cases. (Issue #201 and #208)
* Fix false positive E121 with multiple brackets. (Issue #203)

Change-Id: I99109e83ab46e4db19e27db0711752b34d5084a0

commit_message:
Add API schema for v3 rescue API

By defining the API schema, it is possible to separate the validation
code from the API method. The API method can be more simple.
In addition, a response of API validation error can be consistent for
the whole Nova API.

Partially implements blueprint nova-api-validation-fw

commit_message:
Adding Mako>=0.4.0 to global requirements

Mako>=0.4.0 is default template engine that is used by Pecan.
As well it is in requirements of Pecan:
https://github.com/stackforge/pecan/blob/master/requirements.txt#L2
So it makes sense to add it to global requirements, so we will be
able to use it in other projects without Pecan.

Change-Id: Id7b67a28c882ef00d255118f717857dd3d7021c5

commit_message:
Verify that parsed environment file maps to a dict

An internal unexpected exception is raised while create a stack with an
environment file which only has string content. We should handle the case
and raise the correct error message such as "The environment is not YAML
mapping".

Closes-Bug: #1279609

commit_message:
Switch over to oslosphinx

Having the sphinx theme in the same namespace package
as the production code has been causing issues with
devstack installations. The solution settled on was
to rename oslo.sphinx to oslosphinx because oslo.sphinx
is not a "production" library.

See the linked bug report for more background details.

Closes-Bug: #1277168
Change-Id: I220b8901cef36499e91b92719f1e8e5461a95e92

commit_message:
Switch over to oslosphinx

Having the sphinx theme in the same namespace package
as the production code has been causing issues with
devstack installations. The solution settled on was
to rename oslo.sphinx to oslosphinx because oslo.sphinx
is not a "production" library.

See the linked bug report for more background details.

Closes-Bug: #1277168
Change-Id: I419fe50d66fa0c1ac48deca2286ae7c4b922d72d

subject: Fix tee statement for catching tempest output
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-02-13 23:00:00.000000000', 'files': ['driver_certs/cinder_driver_cert.sh'], 'message': "Fix tee statement for catching tempest output

The use of exec and tee doesn't seem to be quite right, and was
unreliable in terms of catching the exit status of the tempest
test as well as not catching the output when things went wrong.

This changes the way we do the redirect and the tee to something
that should be more robust and seems to work reliably in testing.

Change-Id: Ieb9d725839fb8e3f9e2e63a2b7b2e9c7c86713a2
"}]
commit_message:
Fix tee statement for catching tempest output

The use of exec and tee doesn't seem to be quite right, and was
unreliable in terms of catching the exit status of the tempest
test as well as not catching the output when things went wrong.

This changes the way we do the redirect and the tee to something
that should be more robust and seems to work reliably in testing.

Change-Id: Ieb9d725839fb8e3f9e2e63a2b7b2e9c7c86713a2

translated. It requires use of unicode() instead.

revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2014-02-12 13:12:21.000000000', 'files': ['ironic/cmd/api.py'], 'message': "Make ironic-api not single threaded

The ironic-api service is an instance of wsgiref
simple_server.WSGIServer.  This derives from SocketServer.TCPServer,
which requires that SocketServer.ThreadingMixIn be mixed in for it to
become thread'able, however this was not being done when starting the
WSGIServer.

This patch creates a ThreadedSimpleServer class, which is just a mix
of ThreadingMixIn and WSGIServer, so that the ironic-api process

commit_message:
Make ironic-api not single threaded

The ironic-api service is an instance of wsgiref
simple_server.WSGIServer.  This derives from SocketServer.TCPServer,
which requires that SocketServer.ThreadingMixIn be mixed in for it to
become thread'able, however this was not being done when starting the
WSGIServer.

This patch creates a ThreadedSimpleServer class, which is just a mix
of ThreadingMixIn and WSGIServer, so that the ironic-api process
does not block on network IO.

commit_message:
Raises BadRequest for grant_access on ignore_dbs

Reasons:
- Currently, it just logs an informative log in guestagent log, and then
  control shifts to next line, which provides the requested grant.
- This brings the need to raise the exception instead of informative
  logging.

Changes:
- Raises BadRequest if ignore_dbs are requested access instead of
  informative logging into guest-agent logs.

Change-Id: I9df08d04cd42916f3d1f91e05cd4799bb9041eae
Closes-Bug: #1257021

commit_message:
Fix task_manager acquire post landing for c4f2f26ed

In original implementation we used context lib with try/finally
to make sure release_resources will be called even if there was an
exception inside acquire_resources. With c4f2f26ed we broke that
functionality, so this patch intended to fix this.

Closes-Bug: #1279992

commit_message:
Move cinder-volume creation to post-configure

This is actually not what migration is for. If something must happen
before a service is started, that is a post configuration thing that we
should order before enabling/starting/restarting the service.

Os-refresh-config will be changed to run migration after post-configure,
since it is for on-line things, not offline things.

Change-Id: I2c4eccab3010ec91fcd8129951f638b37bc0932a

commit_message:
Remove multipart/form-data file upload

The requests 'files' parameter adds this 'Content-Type: multipart/form-data'
HTTP header and the whole multipart body data get stored with the object.
This also create a memory hog issue because files are loaded in memory before
being actually sent. This patch removes this behavior and restores what was
done before, ie: direct uploading.

This patches also fixes an issue in requests, when used with glance
CooperativeReader it mis-calculates content-length leading to chunked encoding
for raw upload.

Change-Id: Ie5b0a1078bedd33f09c6157f48b5f88116c589fa
Closes-Bug: #1280072
Closes-Bug: #1280275

commit_message:
Rally & Tempest integration (base) - part 1

Use tempest (https://github.com/openstack/tempest) inside rally to
organize base for verification functionality & for benchmarks scenario
based on tempest.

This patch adds ability to install Tempest tests (no parameters needs)
and to verify the specified cloud (takes a deploy_id as parameter, this
parameter is now optional). For now, there are smoke tests.

Usage:
rally-manage tempest install - install tempest tests
rally verify start --deploy-id=<deploy_id> - start cloud verification

Change-Id: I70bb37476dd2d12370ea77156adab3ceaddb93cb
Related: blueprint tempest-verification

commit_message:
Look for local.json in preference to config.json.

We've had a long standing ugliness where config.json was edited by
devtest to set the ssh username, and then when one commits a
tripleo-image-elements change, it would include your username. This is
undesirable :).

Change-Id: I3129bf638e519f2b03a05cae482e26fd5aef40b1

commit_message:
Remove rootwrap from incubator

oslo.rootwrap now fully graduated to a standalone library, and all three
consuming projects (Nova, Cinder and Neutron) use the library as of the
Icehouse release. There is no need to maintain the frozen code copy in
oslo-incubator anymore.

Implements bp remove-rootwrap

revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2014-02-12 19:29:04.000000000', 'files': ['tox.ini'], 'message': 'Remove tox locale overrides

* tox.ini: The LANG, LANGUAGE and LC_ALL environment overrides were
introduced originally during the testr migration in an attempt to be
conservative about the possibility that locale settings in the
calling environment could cause consistency problems for test runs.
In actuality, this should be unnecessary and any place where it does
cause issues ought to be considered an actual bug. Also, having
these in the configuration actively causes older pip to have
problems with non-ASCII content in some package metadata files under
Python 3, so drop it now.

Change-Id: I840f950d2e9f6e1e40af578900e92cedf8f14295
Closes-Bug: #1277495
'}]
commit_message:
Remove tox locale overrides

* tox.ini: The LANG, LANGUAGE and LC_ALL environment overrides were
introduced originally during the testr migration in an attempt to be
conservative about the possibility that locale settings in the
calling environment could cause consistency problems for test runs.
In actuality, this should be unnecessary and any place where it does
cause issues ought to be considered an actual bug. Also, having
these in the configuration actively causes older pip to have
problems with non-ASCII content in some package metadata files under
Python 3, so drop it now.

Change-Id: I840f950d2e9f6e1e40af578900e92cedf8f14295
Closes-Bug: #1277495

commit_message:
Temporarily cap swiftclient version to fix glance gate failure

Recent python-swiftclient 2.0 release caused wide range gate failure,
due to glance failed to update image to swift backend store. And then vm
refuse to boot with corrupted image, and then massive devstack failure.

Temporarily cap swiftclient version to revive gate jobs until proper
fix.

Related-bug: 1280072
Change-Id: I0604594a0ccc04cfcf120c1004ac63d1cc7c8e14

commit_message:
Treating blanked out config values as defaults for cluster templates

If a dashboard user blanks out a value on the service config tabs
of the cluster-template creation form, the dashboard treats those
as their default values rather than an empty config (which causes
errors).

Fixes:  bug #1212354

Change-Id: If4b720045e78e1d65156c03f75a0cc93706d9015

commit_message:
Run tests in parallel as much as possible

The rpc unit tests have dependencies between tests that make it
impossible to run them in parallel right now, and because that
module is deprecated it doesn't make sense to spend a lot of
effort fixing the problems.  In order to test the other modules
in parallel, we now do two test runs: one in parallel for
everything but rpc, and one serialized for rpc.

Closes-Bug: #1272035

Change-Id: I85ae00b0180bb6fdc760c97882e4e7901e9db2ef

commit_message:
Rename EXTRA_ELEMENTS to SEED_DIB_EXTRA_ARGS

In boot-seed-vm we had a special variable that wasn't consistent with
the rest of devtest - it was only used there, not for other images we
build, and without namespaceing thats at best confusing. Also
cloud-init-nocloud is required for the seed, so there was no point
having it be optional.

Change-Id: Iecfba0cfa495c03c1d3e0495ec38274ee6407ab6

Teach cache-url to handle file:// URIs.

places, by ignoring curl's inability to determine an HTTP status code
for them.

commit_message:
Moved online node checking to before validation task

Here we are fixing two problems

* when we deploy cluster where we have
  offline nodes, we don't want to lock
  cluster's settings
* we should skip all validation in case
  of separate deployment/provisioning

Closes-bug: #1279790
Closes-bug: #1260629
Change-Id: If59940c6bd350e9a74daf9da2efafcba2f583099

commit_message:
Remove glance_notifications from notification_topic

The default notification_topic in Glance has been changed from
'glance_notifications' to 'notifications' in grizzly-2.

Ceilometer was configured to also listen on the
'glance_notifications' notification_topic in addition to
'notifications' to patch this bug. It shouldn't anymore.

Change-Id: I3d797c7e849319a1e20ef3ecbf158e8b8579d450
Closes-bug: #1273876
(cherry picked from commit 924f18ffae174847d4c3d5ec5d5ae4241c9dd897)

commit_message:
Get rid object model `dict` methods part 6

Currently unified object model supports dict-like behavior of objects.
This behavior will be removed in the future so it's necessary to
change Ironic's code to use object attributes as attributes instead of
dictionary keys.

We don't actually remove the interface due to that Oslo might
introduce UOM in future together with this methods and we hide dict
interface from the objects since it has been deprecated.

Change-Id: Ib8662dd9950d5745dd390127b6954dd06c004eab
Closes-Bug: #1256260

commit_message:
Temporarily cap swiftclient version to fix upload error

Recent python-swiftclient 2.0 release caused wide range gate failure,
due to glance failed to update image to swift backend store. And then vm
refuse to boot with corrupted image, and then massive devstack failure.

Temporarily cap swiftclient version to revive gate jobs until proper
fix.

Change-Id: Ia282c21136cca55a018e8ccf3b02f97fcd2e1f28
Partial-Bug: 1280072

commit_message:
Horizon performance tuning

Closes-Bug: #1277292

Some optimizations for Apache/WSGI settings aimed to improve
Apache and Horizon performance:
    - Apache MPM switched from 'prefork' to 'event' for RH-like
      systems
    - Apache/WSGI parameters configuration based on server's
      hardware

Change-Id: Idbd3ccaf05d9ad4a1e8206facece0c53a3fd90e7

commit_message:
Specify CIDR netmask for each VIP

Explicitly setting the netmask for each VIP works around a bug
in Pacemaker where an incorrect netmask is calculated. This
subsequently sets an incorrect broadcast address.

Change-Id: Icf208eff1be27765611500ae0e71ead122a7c4ce
Closes-bug: #1277614

commit_message:
Port to oslo.messaging

* Remove openstack.common.rpc module and implement oslo.messaging
usage instead of that.
* Remove openstack.common.notifier (except api) as it is part of
oslo.messaging now.
* Remove zmq_receiver as a part of oslo.messaging too.

Implements: blueprint oslo-messaging
Change-Id: I4855826b2435b96bcf22ada239d17fa6d0837184

subject: If Cinder crashes during a migration or retype (where data is moved and the operation can take a long time), the storage ends up with multiple copies of the same volume which requires storage admin intervention. Now we maintain a list of pending operations which is backed up in admin metadata. A periodic task reviews the list and removes volume copies whose copy operation completed. When Cinder comes up, we check the admin metadata and rebuild the list.

commit_message:
If Cinder crashes during a migration or retype (where data is moved and
the operation can take a long time), the storage ends up with multiple
copies of the same volume which requires storage admin intervention. Now
we maintain a list of pending operations which is backed up in admin
metadata. A periodic task reviews the list and removes volume copies
whose copy operation completed. When Cinder comes up, we check the admin
metadata and rebuild the list.

Change-Id: I27df5cfa0b0af67f8c45bc3f73a436a5d3afca50
Closes-Bug: #1278035

The aforementioned method is used in the following cases:
1. When a instance is deleted
2. When a rescue instance is created or used

In patch https://review.openstack.org/#/c/60259/ the unique VM
name was saved on the config spec so that the VM ref can be accessed
via FindAllByUuid. This change makes use of that when the VM is to

according to the unique VM name.

Change-Id: I1f00f8711713a41bb99e9a4fd9c78f68755eee25
'}]
commit_message:
VMware: improve performance when using get_vm_ref_from_name

The aforementioned method is used in the following cases:
1. When a instance is deleted
2. When a rescue instance is created or used

In patch https://review.openstack.org/#/c/60259/ the unique VM
name was saved on the config spec so that the VM ref can be accessed
via FindAllByUuid. This change makes use of that when the VM is to
be accessed by the name.

In addition to using the FindAllByUuid the VM ref is also cached
according to the unique VM name.

When a VM is deleted the cache is purged for the vm_name and UUID.

Change-Id: I1f00f8711713a41bb99e9a4fd9c78f68755eee25

commit_message:
Implements checking ring file existence on recon

When checking ring md5 integrity with swift recon if ring
file does not exist, swift-recon will give a stack trace.
This change will check if file exists, if ring file is not
found will print out url of server the ring file was not found on.

Change-Id: I7daafdb0aa6016038d08be5e92092bca60997a8a

commit_message:
Add assertRaisesRegexp method to common test.py

The assertRaisesRegexp method was added to unittest framework in
python 2.7, so we need similar method to use it in python 2.6
environment.

Add assertRaisesRegexp method which asserts that message
in a raised Exception matches a regexp.

Change-Id: I263152d8863ca5ba1dffbe3b1a8c64e4c1bee137

commit_message:
Transition to alembic migration with oslo migration tool

1.Extends heat-manage usage for alembic common commands
For reference refer to: https://alembic.readthedocs.org/en/latest/api.html
2. Compatible with old usage
   heat-manage db_sync - will upgrade database
   heat-manage db_version
3. Improve tests coverage for heat-manage cmd util
4. Create sqlite database for tests from metadata
   sqlite doesnot support alter statements, and sqlalchemy-migrate was
   was patched to do that

Change-Id: Ifdee3c65c3d15bf84eaa68e0e45342b10670bb73
oslo-incubator: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/59433/
Blueprint: oslo-migration-toolkit

commit_message:
Add the ability to get notified of connection loss

When joining a group it is common that the entity
joining that group would like to know if it has somehow
lost that group membership if certain conditions such
as disconnection occur, to accomodate this allow for the
driver to have a list of callbacks which will be automatically
called if the connection is lost.

Change-Id: Iab6acbc6b2934998e51f0618ec66962d77a6ce1c

commit_message:
Use reload from imp module for Python 3 compat

The reload function used to be a built-in in Python 2, but was changed
in Python 3 to be a function of the imp module. That change was
backported to Python 2.6, so it can be accessed from there across all
supported versions.

Change-Id: If37fc0b900f4e289dd8c2633df30e2bf4282d0a9

commit_message:
Make prune compute_node_stats configurable

Nova compute manager will periodically prune metrics for
compute_node_stats, if there are some metrics did not update on
time, those metrics will be pruned.

For some cases, always prune metrics is not acceptable. i.e. I put
some metrics which only need update once to compute_node_stats and
want compute_node_stats keep this value for me. But those metrics
were always pruned by periodic task.

DocImpact
This patch was adding a parameter prune_compute_node_stats to decide
if prune compute_node_stats periodically or not, default value is
True.

Change-Id: I75f925bbd9c1e0d2bf4caed528148db76d8b2be4
Closes-Bug: #1269655

commit_message:
Use timestamp in periodic tasks

All time related data in periodic tasks are in seconds.
Therefore creating datetime objects only adds overhead to the module.
This patch replaces all datetime objects with utc timestamps in periodic_tasks.
Changes to test scripts were made accordingly.

Change-Id: I5bf77fba26aac62856fe30585577b7cf66dd6257

Remove glance_notifications from notification_topic

The default notification_topic in Glance has been changed from
'glance_notifications' to 'notifications' in grizzly-2.

Ceilometer was configured to also listen on the
'glance_notifications' notification_topic in addition to
'notifications' to patch this bug. It shouldn't anymore.

Currently, httplib implementation does not support SSL certificate

and 100-continue thing is still missing from requests, though those are

Requests now takes care of:
* proxy configuration (get_environ_proxies),

commit_message:
Port to python-requests

Currently, httplib implementation does not support SSL certificate
verification. This patch fixes this. Note that ssl compression parameter
and 100-continue thing is still missing from requests, though those are
lower priority.

Requests now takes care of:
* proxy configuration (get_environ_proxies),
* chunked encoding (with data generator),
* bulk uploading (with files dictionary),
* SSL certificate verification (with 'insecure' and 'cacert' parameter).

This patch have been tested with requests 1.1.0 (CentOS 6) and requests
2.2.1 (current version).

Change-Id: Ib5de962f4102d57c71ad85fd81a615362ef175dc
Closes-Bug: #1199783
DocImpact
SecurityImpact

subject: Syncing policy engine from oslo-incubator
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2014-02-13 08:33:24.000000000', 'files': ['keystone/openstack/common/policy.py'], 'message': 'Syncing policy engine from oslo-incubator

Syncing policy module - commit a53c4dc
Includes patch 0da5de6 implementing Blueprint policy-constant-check

python update.py --nodeps --base keystone --dest-dir ../keystone/ --modules policy

-----
Adds the ability to check any resource's field against a constant
(literal, or string) in the policy.json file.

For instance, I can ensure that only users with field `enabled` set to
False can be deleted with the following rule:
"identity:delete_user": "False:%(target.user.enabled)s",

Or that only the `Member` role can be granted:
"identity:create_grant": "'Member':%(target.role.name)s",
-----

Change-Id: I054271306f20aac47ce5e9dac594bc1989fee56d
Implements: blueprint policy-constant-check
'}]
commit_message:
Syncing policy engine from oslo-incubator

Syncing policy module - commit a53c4dc
Includes patch 0da5de6 implementing Blueprint policy-constant-check

python update.py --nodeps --base keystone --dest-dir ../keystone/ --modules policy

-----
Adds the ability to check any resource's field against a constant
(literal, or string) in the policy.json file.

For instance, I can ensure that only users with field `enabled` set to
False can be deleted with the following rule:
"identity:delete_user": "False:%(target.user.enabled)s",

Or that only the `Member` role can be granted:
"identity:create_grant": "'Member':%(target.role.name)s",
-----

Change-Id: I054271306f20aac47ce5e9dac594bc1989fee56d
Implements: blueprint policy-constant-check

commit_message:
Add DB mappings with NSX logical routers

This patch introduces DB mappings between neutron and NSX router,
thus not requiring anymore the Neutron router ID to be equal to the
NSX one.

This change is needed for enabling asynchronous operations in
the NSX plugin.

This patch also performs NVP/NSX renaming where appropriate, and
fixes delete router logic causing a 500 HTTP error to be returned
when a Neutron internal error occurs.

Related to blueprint nvp-async-backend-communication
Related to blueprint nicira-plugin-renaming

Change-Id: Ib0e9ed0f58e7fa3497a93e9cd3baa9cb81ad797b

Update to new hp3parclient

cinder driver and it's unit tests.  This patch is the first in
2 patches that are need to land.  We are breaking this up into
2 patches to avoid breaking continuous deployment.

next patch will update the low end to 3.0.

- Use a static set of finished states instead of creating a new
  list everytime the _done_futures function is called.

Change-Id: I3ca8057ea8047359bf99a6acb00b3b6fd4d75f92

commit_message:
Some small async utils tweaks

- Renames waiter to any waiter (since its event will be triggered
  on any result/exception/cancellation).
- Import _base and use that instead of going through futures._base.
- Use a static set of finished states instead of creating a new
  list everytime the _done_futures function is called.

Change-Id: I3ca8057ea8047359bf99a6acb00b3b6fd4d75f92

commit_message:
Inject rather than read-out the virt power key.

Currently we make a throwaway key when using the virtual power
manager. This doesn't work all that well - users authorised_key files
get huge - and it doesn't work at all for Tripleo-CI.

Change-Id: I93191f8716a9e77da789a12c531ffa00bcd6cd5b

commit_message:
Replace nonexistent mock assert methods with real ones

Methods like assert_not_called, assert_called_once, assert_called do
not exist, they generated on the fly (dummy) and don't assert anything.
This patch replaces each of nonexistent method calls with real.

commit_message:
Log IPMI power on/off timeouts

Ported from nova: Iecd6fadb2b653f4ccbe75882c2ef85812b334e8d

Added log messages for cloud operators so that they can tell when an
attempt to turn a device on or off via IPMI has failed after the
configured number of attempts.

This should help operators diagnose issues on devices that respond
slowly to IPMI commands. The failure to repeatedly change the device
power state is now logged precisely along with the cause, where
before operators had to diagnose the issue through trace log captures.

Change-Id: I06cd432c72d72f5abe8cd5941e4d5844c66c1482

commit_message:
Add support for user/admin permissions in endpoints

Instead of storing the endpoints as a single admin credentials dictionary
(containing the username, password etc.) we should be able to store several
endpoints which can be possibly returned from the deploy object, as well as
the information whether these endpoints have the admin permission or not.
If not, then the deployment is going to be used with the predefined set of
users (that will be implemented next). If there is an admin endpoint, then
the users for benchmarking will be generated (the "admin" role).
This information now gets stored in a dictionary of form:

    "endpoints": [
        {"username": ..., "password": ...,
         "tenant_name": ..., "auth_url": ..., "permission": "admin|user"},
        {"username": ..., "password": ...,
         "tenant_name": ..., "auth_url": ...,
         "permission": "admin|user"},
        ...
    ]

Blueprint benchmarking-with-predefined-users

Change-Id: If36e33e89daa036bd4b0d7db8e2d3b5b5b0f4aca

commit_message:
Remove s3_token functional tests

The s3_token middleware was moved to keystoneclient but the tests
were left to ensure backwards compatibility. The tests have passed
since then and the keystoneclient of the s3_token middleware has
already diverged that causes the tests to fail.

The functional tests are removed and replaced with a test to
ensure that the symbols are forwarded properly.

bp s3-token-to-keystoneclient

Change-Id: Ie1cea741d33400eaa4d4afc7206a3ba1db9a4573

commit_message:
Support TripleO-CI for overcloud builds.

For Tripleo-CI we can't generate the key in the VM and hand it out,
because we have restricted access to the machine. Plus, this has been
ugly forever. Pass an SSH key in, rather than pulling one out.

Change-Id: I1def0757758e30e63891ff099106dac158bd8d83

commit_message:
Fixup missing variables for CI.

For CI we had a number of (tightly related) missing variables:
 - The SSH key has to be passed in, not generated in-instance
 - The host is not 192.168.122.1
 - The arch etc all come from the test environment the test is
   running on so we need to read them from the JSON.

Change-Id: Ia373cd2007750a2ce5ad0b1ee18cf3c44591d9dc
Co-Authored-By: Robert Collins <rbtcollins@hp.com>

commit_message:
Allow setting of publish directory

You can now set the publication directory for a book. This will
allow to make more generic Jenkins jobs since we can now say for example
that api-quick-start-onepager-external gets published as
api-quick-start.

Fix publishing so that books published to trunk or havana etc are
copied to the proper subdirectory of publish-docs.

Change-Id: Ifb45a352e6f803321dcfcfcc5f8f17b7876f209b

commit_message:
Stop catting tempest.config during tempest setup

This commit removes the 'cat tempest.config' from lib/tempest. There
is no reason to cat it as part of running devstack because the file
is and can be interacted with after devstack finishes running. To
prevent a loss of information in the gate this change should be
coupled with devstack-gate change: Ifb36918cd0d686cb3865f5322cd62c209acaaf30
which copies the tempest.config file with the other test artifacts.

Change-Id: Ia01cd53660b3490ea9faa9e9c746bafd9df12a9b

commit_message:
Move every rally command to its own module

Move all the currently supported rally commands (i.e. deployment, task,
use) and their equivalent tests that are described as classes in
the 'main.py' module (and 'test_main.py' module), to separate modules in
a new directory. This is done for organizing the code of the rally command
line utility, before it become too big.

Implements: blueprint rally-show-command
Change-Id: I5982f854dfe64604ae112d93fb7ea68f72657b98

commit_message:
Add samples to serve API through Apache mod_wsgi

The default API service (ironic.cmd.api) uses the wsgiref library.

Some deployers may want to serve the API through apache/httpd instead.

This patch adds application hooks to use with mod_wsgi, and a sample
apache2 config file to demonstrate its use with debian-based distros.

Change-Id: I44cd8e0941c350a6e5c16cf2d068c3e8d684ab47
Related-bug: #1279206

commit_message:
Node power state is not printed after set

As of commit 4676d823a8a35 to Ironic, the API for changing Node power
state no longer returns a body. With no return body, there is nothing
to print in the CLI after requesting the power state change.

This patch removes the print-out of an empty table when the CLI
set-node-power-state command is issued.

Change-Id: If1fb035bdf83e36e3a6a13e639efadc370c40887
Related-bug: #1270160

commit_message:
Add topic to the change_node_maintenance_mode() RPC method

Topic is used by the distributed hashing algorithm in order to know to
which conductor it should route the RPC messages to. All the methods in
the rpcapi should support passing a topic to it.

commit_message:
raise SystemExit instead of calling exit()

exit is a constant meant to be used in the interpreter, not in code:

    >>> print(exit)
    Use exit() or Ctrl-D (i.e. EOF) to exit
    >>> exit()

Change-Id: I35825c81fb33eb7ab6b8bd7279110b2ee3271ea3

commit_message:
Fix race condition when changing node states

To fix race condition we're adding a mechanism of background task
execution in conductor. The conductor will get synchrozed AMQP call,
reserve lock, start the background task and return empty response to
the API. In case when lock cannot be acquired or background tasks pool
is full, the exception is sent back to the API and the task is not
started.

Also the patch adds an ability to control resource locks manually.
This feauture used to release lock in the end of background task.

Change-Id: I4095de2d82058ea5e052531698e67a0947424435
Closes-Bug: #1259910

reviewers: [{'_account_id': 3, 'name': 'Jenkins', 'username': 'jenkins'}, {'_account_id': 642, 'name': 'Matt Dietz', 'email': 'matthew.dietz@gmail.com', 'username': 'cerberus'}, {'_account_id': 1247, 'name': 'Mark McLoughlin', 'email': 'markmc@redhat.com', 'username': 'markmc'}, {'_account_id': 1501, 'name': 'Phil Day', 'email': 'philip.day@hp.com', 'username': 'philip-day'}, {'_account_id': 5441, 'name': 'Andrew Laski', 'email': 'andrew@lascii.com', 'username': 'alaski'}, {'_account_id': 9578, 'name': 'DB Datasets CI', 'email': 'turbo-hipster@lists.rcbops.com', 'username': 'turbo-hipster', 'tags': ['SERVICE_USER']}]
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2014-02-13 12:27:05.000000000', 'files': ['nova/tests/scheduler/fakes.py', 'nova/scheduler/host_manager.py'], 'message': "Don't allow compute_node free_disk_gb to be None

As part of commit 5668870, we now explicitly guard against the case
free_disk_gb is None or unset. However, this should never happen
since resource tracker always sets it and guarding against this case
isn't actually needed to fix the bug in question.

Also, simplify the code a little to make the intent more clear. We
assume that free_disk_gb is always set, but we want to use
disk_available_least where the driver has set it. The case where
disk_available_least is less than free_disk_gb is the exceptional
case we want to guard against.

Change-Id: I3973eab6b4ca016df546de8b57245fc0d0f03a80
"}]
commit_message:
Don't allow compute_node free_disk_gb to be None

As part of commit 5668870, we now explicitly guard against the case
free_disk_gb is None or unset. However, this should never happen
since resource tracker always sets it and guarding against this case
isn't actually needed to fix the bug in question.

Also, simplify the code a little to make the intent more clear. We
assume that free_disk_gb is always set, but we want to use
disk_available_least where the driver has set it. The case where
disk_available_least is less than free_disk_gb is the exceptional
case we want to guard against.

Change-Id: I3973eab6b4ca016df546de8b57245fc0d0f03a80

commit_message:
Add Fedora DHCP interfaces via udev rules

Updates the dhcp-all-interfaces element so that
we add new DHCP interfaces using a udev rule
instead of a systemd service.

The previous approach (using the systemd service)
was proving to be problematic when used with
the new Fedora constistent network naming
convention rules (em1, em2, etc.). We aren't using
these device names as a default yet... but we will
need to soon and when we do udev rules seem to be the
best way to avoid racy behaviour when calling
dhcp-all-interfaces.sh from the systemd service.

Change-Id: I87e0aed1f34718e896bd414388886a1f1073b0c0

subject: Support adding DHCP interfaces one at a time.
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2014-02-12 17:01:00.000000000', 'files': ['elements/dhcp-all-interfaces/install.d/dhcp-all-interfaces.sh'], 'message': "Support adding DHCP interfaces one at a time.

Refactors dhcp-all-interfaces.sh so that if an optional
INTERFACE argument (the first argument) is passed to the script
it only inspects that single interface. If no argument is
passed then the previous default behaviour use used which
causes all interfaces to be inspected.

Also sets PATH so that the commands within the script
can all be found if it isn't set properly (/sbin/ip, /bin/cat, etc.)

This is a move towards using udev rules to add these types
of interfaces automatically.

Change-Id: Ia482c1d3ddce0f0d8d77f9bc3ac76d6924640715
"}]
commit_message:
Support adding DHCP interfaces one at a time.

Refactors dhcp-all-interfaces.sh so that if an optional
INTERFACE argument (the first argument) is passed to the script
it only inspects that single interface. If no argument is
passed then the previous default behaviour use used which
causes all interfaces to be inspected.

Also sets PATH so that the commands within the script
can all be found if it isn't set properly (/sbin/ip, /bin/cat, etc.)

This is a move towards using udev rules to add these types
of interfaces automatically.

Change-Id: Ia482c1d3ddce0f0d8d77f9bc3ac76d6924640715

subject: Propogate cacert and insecure flags to glanceclient
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-02-11 17:08:36.000000000', 'files': ['ceilometer/image/glance.py'], 'message': 'Propogate cacert and insecure flags to glanceclient

Fixes bug 1278973

Previously, the insecure flag was only propagated to the keystoneclient
while the cacert flag was only propagated to the keystoneclient and
the ceilometerclient used by alarming.

Since the glanceclient also supports these options, these flags should
be propogated to it also to avoid SSL cert verification failures when the
central agent calls out to glance over https.

Change-Id: I967ba080a4011a54b5789ca0fc20cb9a37dafb15
'}]
commit_message:
Propogate cacert and insecure flags to glanceclient

Fixes bug 1278973

Previously, the insecure flag was only propagated to the keystoneclient
while the cacert flag was only propagated to the keystoneclient and
the ceilometerclient used by alarming.

Since the glanceclient also supports these options, these flags should
be propogated to it also to avoid SSL cert verification failures when the
central agent calls out to glance over https.

Change-Id: I967ba080a4011a54b5789ca0fc20cb9a37dafb15

commit_message:
Don't use cfg.CONF in oslo.db

Using of a global config object is something we want to avoid when
making libraries. Parameters must be passed as function/class methods
arguments instead.

In order not to duplicate options declaration in each project, they
have been put into separate options module (which should not be a
part of oslo.db when it's released; we'll probably want to find a
place for it within oslo-incubator).

Partial-Bug: #1263908

Co-authored-by: Victor Sergeyev <vsergeyev@mirantis.com>

Change-Id: Ib5a4e31b4e78e2b4cb807a8c88b8072f4207eb22
